# Dev-only artifacts.
node_modules/
*.zip
.DS_Store
npm-debug.log*
.claude/settings.local.json

# Compiled LevelDB compendium packs are BUILD OUTPUT, not source (2026-07-19).
# `packs/_source/**` is the source; the release workflow runs `build:packs`
# before zipping, so the compiled dirs are rebuilt for every release and were
# never read from git. Committing them only produced timestamp churn, binary
# bloat, and dirty repos whenever a Foundry world held the LevelDB locks.
# They are still SHIPPED in module.zip — Foundry reads compiled LevelDB and
# cannot read packs/_source at runtime — just not tracked.
# Run `npm run build:packs` after cloning, or compendiums will be empty.
packs/*
!packs/_source/

# ACKS rules extracts are LOCAL-ONLY (licensed book text; purged from all
# repo histories 2026-07-16). They live in C:\Proj\acks-rules\<module-id>\ —
# these armor patterns guard against accidental re-adds.
docs/RULES.md
docs/PROFICIENCIES.md
docs/ACKS-Reactions-Reference.md
